Definition.WordDefinition:
Condensate \Con*den"sate\, a. [L. condensatus, p. p. of condensare. See {Condense}, v. t.] Made dense; condensed. [1913 Webster]
Water . . . thickened or condensate. --Peacham. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Condensate \Con*den"sate\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Condensated}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Condensating}.] To condense. [R.] --Hammond. [1913 Webster]
condensate n : atmospheric moisture that has condensed because of cold [syn: {condensation}]
